anslations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"quarter, lodging"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"inn, residence, hostel"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"food served to a guest"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to descend, to come down, to go down","examples":[{"text":"يَعْلَمُ مَا يَلِجُ فِى ٱلۡأَرۡضِ وَمَا يَخْرُجُ مِنْهَا وَمَا يَنْزِلُ مِنَ ٱلسَّمَآءِ وَمَا يَعْرُجُ فِيهَا وَهُوَ ٱلرَّحِيمُ ٱلۡغَفُورُ","english":"He knows whatever goes into the earth and whatever comes out of it, and whatever descends from the sky and whatever ascends into it. And He is the Most Merciful, All-Forgiving."}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to descend, to come down, to go down; to send down, to take down","examples":[{"text":"وَإِنَّهُ لَتَنْزِيلُ رَبِّ ٱلْعَالَمِينَ نَزَلَ بِهِ ٱلرُّوحُ ٱلْأَمِينُ","english":"This is certainly a revelation from the Lord of all worlds, The Trustworthy Spirit [i.e., Gabriel] has brought it down."}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to alight, to get off"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to stay, to dwell"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to settle (down somewhere)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to send down, to take down","examples":[{"text":"وَلَئِن سَأَلْتَهُم مَن نَزَّلَ مِنَ السَّمَاءِ مَاءً فَأَحْيَا بِهِ الْأَرْضَ مِن بَعْدِ مَوْتِهَا لَيَقُولُنَّ اللَّهُ","english":"And if you ask them who sends down rain from the sky, giving life to the earth after its death, they will surely say, “Allah!” Say, “Praise be to Allah!” In fact, most of them do not understand."}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to reveal","examples":[{"text":"إِنَّا نَحْنُ نَزَّلْنَا عَلَيْكَ الْقُرْآنَ تَنْزِيلًا","english":"Lo! We, even We, have revealed unto thee the Qur'an, a revelation."}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to download"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":null}